            "author_info": {
                "name": "Neil Highnam",
                "href": "/profile/Neil-Highnam"
            },
            "answer_text": "It becomes thinner because it's drying out. A large part of fruit and vegetables is water: a banana is around 75% water. This water bulks out the fruit. The longer the banana sits around (plucked) the more water it loses and the thinner the skin gets as the water it contains evaporates. Think about how small dried fruit is compared to fresh. ",
